Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Berkeley Tuolumne Camp
Description: A family camp run by the city of Berkeley located just outside of Yosemite National Park that was a destination for East Bay families for hiking, swimming, exploring, and relaxing.

Name: Dolores Park
Description: A well known park in the heart of San Francisco's Mission District with a panoramic view of the city, a playground, tennis and basketball courts, and space for picnics.

Name: Oracle Park
Description: The home ballpark of the San Francisco Giants baseball team since 2000. It's located right next to the San Francisco Bay.

Name: Monterey Bay Aquarium
Description: An aquarium that has a wide range of exhibits featuring local and exotic marine life. It's also known for its extensive ocean conservation work and research labs.

Name: Sibley Volcanic Regional Preserve
Description: Sibley Volcanic Regional Preserve is an East Bay regional park created at the site of a 10-million year old volcano. Situated in the rolling hills of Oakland, it's surrounded by Eucalyptus tree and is a grazing spot for cattle during the spring, and is a very popular hiking spot for East Bay residents.
